    <bioghist>
      <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
      <p>Walter Reade Hardin Jr., Virginia Tech graduate and U. S.
         Army veteran, was born on February 20, 1917. The son of Walter
         Reade and Mattie Young Hardin, he attended Virginia Tech as a
         cadet majoring in business administration. A member of the
         band, as well as the Bachelor, Cotillion and Roanoke clubs,
         Hardin graduated in 1941. During World War II, he served as a
         captain in the U. S. Army. In 1952, he married Mary McIntosh
         Holland. Hardin died on July 17, 1985 and is buried in the
         Christ Church Episcopal Cemetery, Eastville, Virginia.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>This collection contains materials collected by Virginia
         Tech student and band member Walter Reade Hardin Jr.
         Apparently removed from a scrapbook, the collection contains a
         number of mementos associated with Virginia Tech social
         affairs (including dances and concerts); various photos of
         cadet and band groups, classmates, and events surrounding the
         1938 homecoming football game with the University of Virginia;
         and a small assortment of newspaper clippings.</p>
    </scopecontent>
